The set $A{}$ of positive integers satisfies the following conditions:\begin{itemize}
\item If a positive integer $n{}$ belongs to $A{}$, then $2n$ also belongs to $A{}$;
\item For any positive integer $n{}$ there exists an element of $A{}$ divisible by $n{}$;
