Determine all functions $f \colon \mathbb{N} \to \mathbb{N}_0$ for which the following conditions all hold:
\begin{itemize}
    \item For all positive integers $n$, $f(n) = f(F_n)$;
    \item For all positive integers $m$ and $n$, $f(mn) = f(m) + f(n)$;
    \item $f(5) = 1$.
\end{itemize}
Here $\{F_n\}_{\geq 1}$ is the Fibonacci sequence defined by $F_1 = F_2 = 1$ and
$F_{n+2} = F_{n+1} + F_n$ for $n \ge 1$.

A finite amount of ants are walking in a circular table of radius $1$, each having speed $1$. Every time two ants meet they choose a direction, One of the ants turns in that direction and the other ant goes in the opposite direction (both at speed $1$). Assume that there are never $3$ or more ants in the same place. The process ends when all ants fall off the table.
\begin{enumerate}
\item Can the process last forever?
\item Is there a constant $C$, independent of the number of ants, such that all ants will fall after at most $C$ units of time?
\end{enumerate}

Let $S$ be a set with 2002 elements, and let $N$ be an integer with $0 \leq N \leq 2^{2002}$. Prove that it is possible to color every subset of $S$ either black or white so that the following conditions hold:

(a) the union of any two white subsets is white;
(b) the union of any two black subsets is black;
(c) there are exactly $N$ white subsets.

