$9$ people are playing a game, including Tony Wang. The game is as follows:
\begin{itemize}
  \item $9$ people simultaneously place their hand either palm up or palm down. The majority of people that place their hand in the same orientation wins. (As an example, if $5$ people place their hand palm up and $4$ people place their hand palm down, the $5$ people with their hand palm up wins. In the case that all $9$ people place their hand in the same orientation, they all win.)
\end{itemize}
Assuming that each person has an equal chance of placing their hand palm up or down, find the probability of Tony Wang winning the game.

