Show that there exist positive integers $b_1, b_2, \cdots, b_n$ satisfying the following three conditions:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item $a_i \le b_i$ for $i = 1, 2, \dots, n$;
    \item the remainders of $b_1, b_2, \cdots, b_n$ on division by $n$ are pairwise different;
    \item $b_1 + b_2 + \cdots + b_n \le n\left( \frac{n-1}{2} + \left\lfloor \frac{a_1 + a_2 + \cdots + a_n}{n} \right\rfloor \right)$.
\end{enumerate}

